1
00:02:15,679 --> 00:02:17,755
How long you gonna be?.

2
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:28,262
Be right out,

3
00:02:29,358 --> 00:02:31,397
you're a pain!

4
00:02:58,384 --> 00:02:59,463
Hey, American.

5
00:02:59,552 --> 00:03:01,591
I'm still here, gettin' a manicure.

6
00:03:02,721 --> 00:03:05,805
Things okay?.

7
00:03:06,683 --> 00:03:08,889
Gettin' tanned?. Don't get burned!

8
00:03:09,936 --> 00:03:11,893
Bruno's here too.

9
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:14,055
You got a crap body!

10
00:03:15,232 --> 00:03:17,308
Is Bruno here?.

11
00:03:18,193 --> 00:03:19,308
He's over there.

12
00:03:26,618 --> 00:03:28,694
You doin' a lamp?.

13
00:04:38,390 --> 00:04:39,553
It's 2,000.

14
00:04:39,642 --> 00:04:42,642
How much are you
supposed to get this week?.

15
00:04:42,728 --> 00:04:43,842
9,200.

16
00:04:44,729 --> 00:04:47,814
Sure?. It was less last week.

17
00:04:48,942 --> 00:04:50,981
Yes, Don Ciro 9,200.

18
00:04:53,029 --> 00:04:55,151
Another 2,000 euro and we're even.

19
00:04:56,198 --> 00:04:58,237
Don Ciro, don't take all day.

20
00:04:58,325 --> 00:05:00,282
He's slow.

21
00:05:01,411 --> 00:05:03,534
Hurry, so we can go home.

22
00:05:05,582 --> 00:05:07,621
Things okay out there?.

23
00:05:07,708 --> 00:05:08,871
Keep your eyes open.

24
00:05:20,136 --> 00:05:21,334
That's it.

25
00:05:26,559 --> 00:05:28,598
Put paper cups in.

26
00:05:33,690 --> 00:05:34,935
Toilet paper.

27
00:05:42,114 --> 00:05:45,115
- Then, Mom?.
- Some shampoo.

28
00:05:47,286 --> 00:05:48,448
A mozzarella...

29
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,622
Shampoo, not bath oil!

30
00:05:55,752 --> 00:05:58,705
You're rushin' me!

31
00:05:58,796 --> 00:06:00,872
And you're drivin' me crazy!

32
00:06:06,011 --> 00:06:09,095
Hurry up, there are
more groceries to deliver.

33
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:11,220
- Nothing else?.
- No.

34
00:06:15,561 --> 00:06:18,645
- Be back later.
- Don't get yourself lost.

35
00:06:30,157 --> 00:06:32,280
- Simone.
- Toto, what's up?.

36
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:36,244
- What's happening?.
- I'm workin'.

37
00:06:37,456 --> 00:06:40,575
Know what happened?.
They arrested Vitale and Bon Bon.

38
00:06:41,418 --> 00:06:42,532
Really?.

39
00:06:42,627 --> 00:06:45,746
- Got somethin' to eat?.
- Yeah, but it's not mine.

40
00:06:45,838 --> 00:06:47,795
Bye, see you.

41
00:07:04,563 --> 00:07:06,520
Carmela, ma'am!

42
00:07:12,821 --> 00:07:13,983
Hi, Boxer.

43
00:07:41,972 --> 00:07:44,048
Two doses, two doses!

44
00:07:45,058 --> 00:07:47,181
Please, give me a dose!

45
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,432
Gaetano, check it!

46
00:08:28,847 --> 00:08:30,887
One, two, three...

47
00:08:35,228 --> 00:08:36,307
Goodbye.

48
00:08:38,439 --> 00:08:40,479
Don Ciro, be more punctual.

49
00:08:41,442 --> 00:08:43,434
I'll pass it on.

50
00:08:51,785 --> 00:08:52,899
Eleven and twelve.

51
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:55,946
See if he wants coffee.

52
00:08:56,038 --> 00:08:58,114
No, but thank you anyway....

53
00:08:58,207 --> 00:09:00,164
I'll show you out.

54
00:09:00,292 --> 00:09:02,201
Have a good day.

55
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:12,634
Four hundred...

56
00:09:16,932 --> 00:09:18,047
Five hundred.

57
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:21,050
The same amount again?.

58
00:09:22,145 --> 00:09:25,229
I've said a hundred times
I can't manage like this.

59
00:09:26,191 --> 00:09:27,305
Don Carlo...

60
00:09:30,486 --> 00:09:34,483
Did you tell them I can't manage
on this chickenfeed?.

61
00:09:34,698 --> 00:09:37,652
I have to pay rent, lights, water.

62
00:09:38,743 --> 00:09:41,780
I can't survive,
I'm strapped with debts.

63
00:09:41,913 --> 00:09:45,032
- I'll pass it on.
- You always say that!

64
00:09:45,082 --> 00:09:48,036
Are you mockin' me?.

65
00:09:49,169 --> 00:09:50,332
I don't get it!

66
00:09:51,171 --> 00:09:52,416
Listen,

67
00:09:53,298 --> 00:09:55,421
I've got a son to support,

68
00:09:55,509 --> 00:09:58,593
for forty years
I've kept him off the streets,

69
00:09:59,637 --> 00:10:01,677
he's unemployed.

70
00:10:01,764 --> 00:10:04,884
What can I do,
go over to the other side?.

71
00:10:05,851 --> 00:10:09,979
They know, I served you honestly
for forty years.

72
00:10:10,063 --> 00:10:13,230
My wife's in jail,
is this the thanks we get?.

73
00:10:14,109 --> 00:10:17,228
Are we crazy?.
Do I have to raise hell?.

74
00:10:20,489 --> 00:10:21,568
Silvana!

75
00:10:29,956 --> 00:10:31,830
May I?.

76
00:10:34,085 --> 00:10:35,199
Come on in!

77
00:10:36,087 --> 00:10:37,118
Maria!

78
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:41,213
The bill?.

79
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:43,458
Talk to Mom.

80
00:10:49,807 --> 00:10:51,716
Put this in your pocket.

81
00:10:51,892 --> 00:10:53,766
Thank you.

82
00:11:07,406 --> 00:11:09,446
Carabinieri on the street!

83
00:11:20,001 --> 00:11:22,040
He's comin' out!

84
00:11:40,853 --> 00:11:43,770
I'm the best, number one!

85
00:11:43,856 --> 00:11:45,018
So?.

86
00:11:45,941 --> 00:11:47,020
Go, Marco!

87
00:11:47,109 --> 00:11:51,272
- I'll blast these roaches!
- Who do you think you're fighting?.

88
00:11:52,113 --> 00:11:55,233
I'm number one! Tony Montana!

89
00:11:55,366 --> 00:11:57,442
The world is ours!

90
00:11:57,576 --> 00:12:00,530
You don't know
who you're up against!

91
00:12:00,579 --> 00:12:02,655
I'm Tony Montana!

92
00:12:02,789 --> 00:12:05,707
- I'm the powerhouse!
- Yeah!

93
00:12:05,792 --> 00:12:06,871
Come here.

94
00:12:08,837 --> 00:12:10,912
Shit Colombians,

95
00:12:11,005 --> 00:12:12,998
they're everywhere.

96
00:12:13,174 --> 00:12:16,091
See, Colombians everywhere.

97
00:12:19,471 --> 00:12:22,341
You really looked like Scarface.

98
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,892
You were good.

99
00:12:34,985 --> 00:12:37,191
Now it all has to be ours,
the whole world.

100
00:12:38,196 --> 00:12:40,153
Miami, all of it.

101
00:12:54,753 --> 00:12:56,911
My friend, got stuff?.

102
00:13:07,222 --> 00:13:08,467
You got stuff?.

103
00:13:13,645 --> 00:13:16,681
- Got good stuff?.
- You got money?.

104
00:13:16,773 --> 00:13:20,770
- Sure, you got coke?.
- What do you want to pay?.

105
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:22,982
Me?. 50.

106
00:13:24,947 --> 00:13:28,232
- 55, can you do it?.
- No, 55 is too much, 50.

107
00:13:29,325 --> 00:13:31,365
You sure?.

108
00:13:32,328 --> 00:13:34,321
Wait here for me.

109
00:13:43,755 --> 00:13:44,953
Where's Smarty?.

110
00:14:03,565 --> 00:14:04,679
Hey, kid!

111
00:14:18,161 --> 00:14:20,153
Give him the money.

112
00:14:25,626 --> 00:14:28,580
- Is it all here?.
- Yeah.

113
00:14:44,393 --> 00:14:47,263
- Okay?.
- Yes.

114
00:14:50,607 --> 00:14:53,643
- Want to see it?.
- I want to try it.

115
00:14:55,653 --> 00:14:56,898
I gave you the money!

116
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:58,894
Wait!

117
00:15:04,202 --> 00:15:06,195
Open your hand.

118
00:15:10,249 --> 00:15:11,329
It's good.

119
00:15:14,420 --> 00:15:15,665
Give me all of it!

120
00:15:24,929 --> 00:15:26,886
Grab the money!

121
00:16:36,785 --> 00:16:38,908
Giovanni, I brought the kids.

122
00:16:38,996 --> 00:16:40,075
Come in.

123
00:16:44,042 --> 00:16:46,330
You know very well why you're here.

124
00:16:47,211 --> 00:16:50,497
Too much ruckus going on in my area,
because I'm the boss here.

125
00:16:51,382 --> 00:16:52,627
That's just you sayin'.

126
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:56,751
If I had you come here, I know.
No back-talk

127
00:16:57,638 --> 00:16:59,844
or I'll smash your face!

128
00:17:00,807 --> 00:17:04,057
- What happened?.
- For the moment, nothing.

129
00:17:05,019 --> 00:17:06,182
Get me?.

130
00:17:07,021 --> 00:17:11,232
I can't be made to look bad
because of two kids like you.

131
00:17:11,358 --> 00:17:14,478
The next time
I hear anything about you,

132
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:16,565
I'll blow your heads off.

133
00:17:17,447 --> 00:17:20,566
- If it's like you say...
- Shut up when I'm talking.

134
00:17:20,658 --> 00:17:22,781
Then if I come to realize

135
00:17:23,786 --> 00:17:25,909
you're worth something,

136
00:17:25,996 --> 00:17:28,914
which I'll determine and I'll decide,

137
00:17:29,082 --> 00:17:32,000
you can work for me.

138
00:17:32,169 --> 00:17:34,244
Is that clear?.

139
00:17:35,338 --> 00:17:37,247
Show them out.

140
00:17:43,554 --> 00:17:45,593
"I'll smash your face!"

141
00:17:45,681 --> 00:17:47,803
And I'll tear your beard!

142
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:50,759
Without a T-shirt.

143
00:17:50,852 --> 00:17:52,975
"Sweet Pea", looked like a bum.

144
00:17:54,063 --> 00:17:55,142
A real bum.

145
00:17:56,065 --> 00:17:59,315
He is a bum! Did you see
who he sent to get us?.

146
00:18:00,319 --> 00:18:02,395
If that guy's the boss here,

147
00:18:02,487 --> 00:18:04,527
then here we can be the bosses.

148
00:18:06,449 --> 00:18:09,652
If a guy like him is boss here,
this area is ours!

149
00:18:10,661 --> 00:18:12,701
I'll live for 30 years
if he's boss here.

150
00:18:13,914 --> 00:18:16,868
Sure, because he's a retard!

151
00:18:17,042 --> 00:18:21,122
Get it?. I'll live for 30 years.

152
00:18:21,254 --> 00:18:24,125
But he could at least shave!

153
00:18:24,215 --> 00:18:25,330
Shave!

154
00:18:26,342 --> 00:18:28,381
"I'll smash your face!"

155
00:18:29,387 --> 00:18:31,593
Let's go have a snort to spite him.

156
00:18:32,556 --> 00:18:35,640
We've got everything,
we can do like we want.

157
00:18:38,937 --> 00:18:41,890
Anyway, he's a fat shit-ass.

158
00:18:42,065 --> 00:18:44,022
He bugged you?.

159
00:18:44,108 --> 00:18:46,231
He showers once a week!

160
00:18:50,405 --> 00:18:52,445
"I'll blow your heads off! "

161
00:19:17,513 --> 00:19:18,592
Roberto!

162
00:19:28,857 --> 00:19:30,932
Let's go, it's too small.

163
00:19:31,025 --> 00:19:35,069
- But the methane one's big.
- No, it's small.

164
00:19:35,279 --> 00:19:39,407
- Can I finish measuring?.
- No, we're wasting time.

165
00:19:42,536 --> 00:19:46,580
- I have to take some shots.
- What a bore with these pictures!

166
00:19:46,706 --> 00:19:48,615
Let's go!

167
00:19:54,046 --> 00:19:55,955
Just look at this.

168
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:59,047
It's disgusting down there.

169
00:20:08,392 --> 00:20:09,590
Here is perfect.

170
00:20:10,644 --> 00:20:12,553
It's perfect.

171
00:20:12,729 --> 00:20:15,932
We're near the highway,
the trucks can get really close,

172
00:20:16,775 --> 00:20:19,859
they dump the earth
and cover all the water.

173
00:20:20,028 --> 00:20:21,107
Perfect.

174
00:20:23,239 --> 00:20:25,315
Franco, it's 85 meters.

175
00:20:26,158 --> 00:20:28,197
Get the length too.

176
00:20:30,454 --> 00:20:32,411
Come here.

177
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:36,579
Dante.

178
00:20:36,709 --> 00:20:38,749
Hello, everything okay?.

179
00:20:40,963 --> 00:20:43,002
This is Roberto.

180
00:20:46,009 --> 00:20:49,259
- It's time we made room for youth.
- We need new energy.

181
00:20:49,304 --> 00:20:51,343
Take a few more shots.

182
00:20:53,349 --> 00:20:55,388
Did you hear?.

183
00:20:55,476 --> 00:20:57,552
They bombed me,

184
00:20:57,645 --> 00:20:59,602
at the cement plant.

185
00:21:00,772 --> 00:21:02,848
A whole wall came down,

186
00:21:03,692 --> 00:21:04,806
slowly.

187
00:21:04,943 --> 00:21:06,900
Be careful.

188
00:21:06,986 --> 00:21:09,026
Zio resolved it.

189
00:21:09,906 --> 00:21:13,072
I'd forgotten to pay
for some land I'd bought.

190
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:16,236
- An injunction against payment?.
- Yeah!

191
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:18,493
- What do you think?.
- It's fine.

192
00:21:19,372 --> 00:21:23,536
- Can we fill this quarry?.
- Sure can.

193
00:21:23,626 --> 00:21:25,666
Tell Zio it's fine.

194
00:21:25,753 --> 00:21:29,881
Remember, everything clean:
terracing, solid stuff...

195
00:21:30,925 --> 00:21:34,044
Or the redevelopment agency
will break our balls.

196
00:21:34,970 --> 00:21:38,255
Don't worry,
you emptied it and I'll fill it.

197
00:21:47,690 --> 00:21:51,769
All the pieces have to be cut
and the sizes worked out.

198
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:55,896
They want 120 of these.

199
00:22:08,458 --> 00:22:10,534
Six and seven are identical.

200
00:22:14,672 --> 00:22:16,795
Here the satin is cut on the bias.

201
00:22:16,882 --> 00:22:18,875
It's all hand-hemmed.

202
00:22:18,968 --> 00:22:20,925
Is it tough?.

203
00:22:21,011 --> 00:22:24,095
The models aren't hard,
I can do it.

204
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:29,388
Eight hundred items in two months,
is our request.

205
00:22:30,228 --> 00:22:33,312
Keep in mind
we start at 50 euros per item.

206
00:22:34,523 --> 00:22:37,643
You've seen the models,
the price is good,

207
00:22:37,735 --> 00:22:40,652
estimate and make your offers.

208
00:22:41,863 --> 00:22:43,986
Thirty euro, 30 days?.

209
00:22:44,824 --> 00:22:46,900
Don't go any lower.

210
00:22:47,035 --> 00:22:49,110
This is high fashion,
it's not pret-a-porter.

211
00:22:49,161 --> 00:22:51,201
Forty-five, in two months.

212
00:22:53,248 --> 00:22:55,371
- Ms. Zamarion!
- Yes?.

213
00:22:55,459 --> 00:22:57,535
Thirty-eight, forty.

214
00:22:58,378 --> 00:23:00,501
That's a very interesting proposal.

215
00:23:00,588 --> 00:23:02,581
Thirty-five, thirty-five,

216
00:23:02,674 --> 00:23:05,758
excellent workmanship
and delivery times respected.

217
00:23:06,927 --> 00:23:08,920
Thirty, thirty!

218
00:23:17,103 --> 00:23:18,301
Please,

219
00:23:18,396 --> 00:23:21,266
we're not imposing anything!

220
00:23:22,358 --> 00:23:24,516
Did we say thirty, thirty?.

221
00:23:25,653 --> 00:23:27,645
At this point

222
00:23:27,738 --> 00:23:29,730
twenty-eight, thirty!

223
00:23:33,952 --> 00:23:35,944
Thirty, twenty-five!

224
00:23:38,039 --> 00:23:40,161
I can't lose this bid.

225
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:43,409
Come here, there's some bubbly!

226
00:23:46,421 --> 00:23:48,414
Are they coming?.

227
00:23:48,506 --> 00:23:50,713
- I don't think so.
- Why not?.

228
00:23:53,761 --> 00:23:56,715
Five days less for delivery,

229
00:23:56,806 --> 00:23:59,842
we'll have to work overtime,
and I'll do nights...

230
00:23:59,933 --> 00:24:02,009
What's odd about that?.

231
00:24:02,102 --> 00:24:04,141
They're talking overtime pay.

232
00:24:04,229 --> 00:24:06,268
They'll get it!

233
00:24:06,314 --> 00:24:09,398
Am I scared of a little overtime?.

234
00:24:11,444 --> 00:24:13,436
Like the last time?.

235
00:24:13,487 --> 00:24:15,645
Don't worry,
this time it's a sure thing.

236
00:24:18,867 --> 00:24:21,868
- They've lost their trust.
- I know.

237
00:24:21,953 --> 00:24:26,033
- I asked you to talk to them.
- You do it, please.

238
00:24:26,123 --> 00:24:29,208
You're on closer terms,
they respect you.

239
00:24:30,252 --> 00:24:32,292
Do me this favor.

240
00:24:33,422 --> 00:24:35,498
Don't say no, go talk to them.

241
00:24:36,591 --> 00:24:38,584
You know I'm fond of you,

242
00:24:38,676 --> 00:24:40,716
I'll have to make
a gold statue to you!

243
00:24:40,762 --> 00:24:43,679
I'll go down and see the accountant
for the money.

244
00:24:49,061 --> 00:24:52,014
Sorry, how much is this?.

245
00:24:53,023 --> 00:24:54,185
Ten thousand.

246
00:24:56,234 --> 00:24:58,357
It's not enough, I need more.

247
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:00,482
Twice that at least.

248
00:25:01,363 --> 00:25:03,486
Mr. Enzo,
you're already "complicated".

249
00:25:03,574 --> 00:25:05,697
Yes, but for personal affairs.

250
00:25:05,784 --> 00:25:08,701
I need this for work.

251
00:25:08,787 --> 00:25:10,910
I'll give it back in three months.

252
00:25:10,997 --> 00:25:13,914
But this isn't enough.

253
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,158
If you don't need it
and it's not enough,

254
00:25:17,086 --> 00:25:18,248
I'll take it back.

255
00:25:19,129 --> 00:25:20,292
It's best for you.

256
00:25:21,173 --> 00:25:23,331
Don't be like that, listen,

257
00:25:23,425 --> 00:25:25,548
I need at least double!

258
00:25:26,511 --> 00:25:28,468
It's no risk,

259
00:25:28,555 --> 00:25:29,717
you'll earn from it, right?.

260
00:25:30,598 --> 00:25:31,713
What can I say?.

261
00:25:31,807 --> 00:25:34,761
I'll pass it on,
can you make-do for now?.

262
00:25:34,894 --> 00:25:36,933
Yes, I'll take it.

263
00:25:48,364 --> 00:25:50,440
Congratulations, Mr. Pasquale.

264
00:25:50,491 --> 00:25:51,605
Thank you.

265
00:25:52,451 --> 00:25:53,696
We met yesterday.

266
00:25:55,579 --> 00:25:57,820
I need your help.

267
00:26:05,129 --> 00:26:07,252
I am having trouble with work.

268
00:26:09,383 --> 00:26:12,419
I have to get into
haute couture right away,

269
00:26:14,471 --> 00:26:16,510
but for me

270
00:26:17,515 --> 00:26:19,591
it is very difficult.

271
00:26:19,642 --> 00:26:21,765
I need help.

272
00:26:24,980 --> 00:26:27,020
You are

273
00:26:27,941 --> 00:26:30,017
a great master,

274
00:26:30,152 --> 00:26:32,310
you are very important for me.

275
00:26:33,154 --> 00:26:35,194
You teach ten lessons

276
00:26:35,406 --> 00:26:38,323
to workers in my factory.

277
00:26:39,535 --> 00:26:41,658
I pay you in cash,

278
00:26:42,704 --> 00:26:44,780
2,000 euros a lesson

279
00:26:46,750 --> 00:26:47,948
for ten lessons.

280
00:26:48,918 --> 00:26:52,121
We work together,
but no one knows it,

281
00:26:53,172 --> 00:26:55,165
just the two of us.

282
00:26:57,176 --> 00:26:59,215
I need your help.

283
00:27:00,429 --> 00:27:02,338
Think it over.

284
00:27:06,684 --> 00:27:09,685
- What's the cloth like?.
- Come and see.

285
00:27:45,052 --> 00:27:46,250
I've got nothin'!

286
00:27:46,345 --> 00:27:48,384
Don't move!

287
00:28:54,114 --> 00:28:57,150
They must have gone over to his side,

288
00:28:58,034 --> 00:29:01,201
or they'd have arrested
me first and then those other guys.

289
00:29:01,329 --> 00:29:04,495
Believe me?. All of them were there
when I called you.

290
00:29:04,540 --> 00:29:07,457
I said: Check out this car,
it's suspect.

291
00:29:07,543 --> 00:29:09,582
This stuff here is ours.

292
00:29:09,711 --> 00:29:11,668
My gun!

293
00:29:13,715 --> 00:29:16,799
Check this stuff out,
there should be fifty-six.

294
00:29:18,928 --> 00:29:21,086
Good, Toto, this is for you.

295
00:29:25,350 --> 00:29:27,473
How can I get working with you?.

296
00:29:28,311 --> 00:29:30,387
We'll let you know.

297
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:34,729
- Did you turn off the water?.
- Of course!

298
00:29:35,610 --> 00:29:37,851
- Can I help out?.
- No, you'll get wet.

299
00:29:38,737 --> 00:29:39,900
Doesn't matter!

300
00:29:40,864 --> 00:29:42,857
Come and see.

301
00:29:42,950 --> 00:29:44,989
Careful not to slip.

302
00:29:46,077 --> 00:29:50,205
- Is it coming from the well?.
- No, I think it's from the pipe.

303
00:29:50,373 --> 00:29:53,374
Careful, water's coming in.

304
00:29:54,543 --> 00:29:57,461
See if you can close it.

305
00:29:57,546 --> 00:29:59,669
It's closed,
but it's the pipe that...

306
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:08,130
I'd give you a hand, but...

307
00:30:10,057 --> 00:30:11,220
What a great day!

308
00:30:12,059 --> 00:30:14,182
Push it all in one direction.

309
00:30:20,567 --> 00:30:23,520
I thought I'd be having coffee!

310
00:30:23,611 --> 00:30:26,814
- Nice coffee, huh?.
- I'll have some next time.

311
00:30:35,080 --> 00:30:37,119
Totore, things okay?.

312
00:30:38,374 --> 00:30:41,410
- Can I say hi?.
- No, you gotta leave.

313
00:30:41,502 --> 00:30:44,372
Go down with these bags!

314
00:30:45,506 --> 00:30:47,545
You have to move!

315
00:30:48,675 --> 00:30:50,751
Ma'am, go around the other way.

316
00:30:50,802 --> 00:30:53,886
- What's going on?.
- Everything's fine, leave.

317
00:31:14,782 --> 00:31:15,861
Lucia?.

318
00:31:48,062 --> 00:31:49,176
Come closer.

319
00:31:50,231 --> 00:31:53,184
- What's your name?.
- Luigi.

320
00:31:54,443 --> 00:31:57,396
- Are you scared?.
- No.

321
00:31:57,487 --> 00:31:59,645
- Sure?.
- No.

322
00:32:00,531 --> 00:32:01,729
We'll see.

323
00:32:02,783 --> 00:32:05,868
- Are you strong?.
- Yeah!

324
00:32:06,870 --> 00:32:08,993
Let's see how strong you are.

325
00:32:13,126 --> 00:32:15,165
Why are you shaking?.

326
00:32:16,379 --> 00:32:18,206
No?.

327
00:34:24,536 --> 00:34:27,572
- See how strong this kid is.
- Come closer!

328
00:34:35,045 --> 00:34:37,962
- Are you scared?.
- Yes.

329
00:34:55,772 --> 00:34:57,765
Now you're a man.

330
00:35:16,708 --> 00:35:18,783
Nothin'! Everything's okay!

331
00:35:19,877 --> 00:35:23,874
When I did my piercing,
I got an infection.

332
00:35:23,964 --> 00:35:25,921
Let's see.

333
00:35:26,967 --> 00:35:29,043
You went and did it there?.

334
00:35:30,261 --> 00:35:33,262
- I'd like to have it on my eyebrow.
- Stinks.

335
00:35:33,348 --> 00:35:35,423
It's nicer there, you're right.

336
00:35:37,601 --> 00:35:39,641
It's gonna rain.

337
00:35:45,775 --> 00:35:46,890
Everything's okay!

338
00:35:46,985 --> 00:35:49,061
A car's coming!

339
00:35:51,072 --> 00:35:53,064
It went in!

340
00:35:55,242 --> 00:35:57,282
It's going in!

341
00:35:58,245 --> 00:36:00,321
Check out this other one!

342
00:36:02,582 --> 00:36:04,575
Everything's okay!

343
00:36:36,946 --> 00:36:40,066
Sorry I'm late, the Councilman,
City Hall, the traffic...

344
00:36:41,033 --> 00:36:43,191
- My father.
- How do you do.

345
00:36:47,289 --> 00:36:50,373
I'm glad he's with you
you're a good person.

346
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:52,576
He's in your care.

347
00:36:52,669 --> 00:36:54,661
He's a clever guy.

348
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:57,829
I don't doubt that but...

349
00:36:57,923 --> 00:37:00,877
- Having work is important to him.
- Of course.

350
00:37:00,926 --> 00:37:03,962
I tried so hard
to find him work in Naples...

351
00:37:04,054 --> 00:37:07,220
- Where do you work?.
- In the hospital, intensive care.

352
00:37:08,099 --> 00:37:10,222
A bad division.

353
00:37:11,310 --> 00:37:15,557
I tried to get him in,
but I have no connections.

354
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:18,516
He's all set now.

355
00:37:18,609 --> 00:37:21,645
You did something no one else did.

356
00:37:21,737 --> 00:37:23,895
I thank you, you raised him well.

357
00:37:23,989 --> 00:37:25,981
Have you always worked in Naples?.

358
00:37:26,824 --> 00:37:28,983
No, also in Trieste, Udine,

359
00:37:29,952 --> 00:37:32,110
- Venice...
- That's where we're going.

360
00:37:32,204 --> 00:37:35,288
I told him about Venice.

361
00:37:36,291 --> 00:37:39,541
He's excited, it's his first time.

362
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:43,705
Dad, we have a plane.

363
00:37:44,549 --> 00:37:46,671
Did you bring some things?.

364
00:37:46,801 --> 00:37:48,923
What's that, your gym bag?.

365
00:37:49,970 --> 00:37:52,971
- Goodbye.
- He's in your care.

366
00:38:12,907 --> 00:38:16,905
- What do you pay for disposal?.
- Today I'm paying 50.

367
00:38:16,994 --> 00:38:18,157
Your offer?.

368
00:38:19,038 --> 00:38:21,077
We can halve your costs,

369
00:38:21,165 --> 00:38:23,157
25 cents a kilo.

370
00:38:23,250 --> 00:38:25,242
That's good,

371
00:38:25,335 --> 00:38:27,411
but is it all "clean",
like they say in the United States?.

372
00:38:27,462 --> 00:38:29,502
Since it's toxic waste,

373
00:38:29,589 --> 00:38:32,506
certification,
storage and transportation.

374
00:38:34,802 --> 00:38:37,886
- Is there a contract to look over?.
- Of course.

375
00:38:42,059 --> 00:38:44,051
In case you're wondering,

376
00:38:44,144 --> 00:38:46,220
the disposal cycle

377
00:38:46,312 --> 00:38:49,230
goes to the disposal area
in Marcianise.

378
00:38:49,273 --> 00:38:51,313
I'm telling you in fairness.

379
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:53,559
Thank you for the information,

380
00:38:54,445 --> 00:38:56,733
but my only concern
is that it's "clean".

381
00:38:57,573 --> 00:38:59,695
You can rest assured of that.

382
00:38:59,783 --> 00:39:01,859
We can dispose of all the waste

383
00:39:01,993 --> 00:39:04,033
that you produce in a year.

384
00:39:04,871 --> 00:39:06,033
Eight hundred tons.

385
00:39:07,957 --> 00:39:09,036
It's not a problem.

386
00:39:09,125 --> 00:39:10,287
That's a lot.

387
00:39:14,504 --> 00:39:16,544
My concern is disposal.

388
00:39:17,382 --> 00:39:19,624
We serve various companies,
you can check.

389
00:39:20,677 --> 00:39:22,716
I already have!

390
00:39:23,763 --> 00:39:25,755
Don't worry.

391
00:39:26,932 --> 00:39:29,968
As far as I can see,
there's maximum transparency.

392
00:39:30,018 --> 00:39:31,927
Absolutely.

393
00:39:34,189 --> 00:39:37,355
- The warehouses at Teverola?.
- We use them for tires.

394
00:39:38,234 --> 00:39:39,313
Exactly.

395
00:39:39,485 --> 00:39:42,521
Will we put the tannery waste
in the quarry?.

396
00:39:42,613 --> 00:39:45,483
- Don't talk foolishness.
- Where then?.

397
00:39:45,574 --> 00:39:47,697
Check the European catalogue.

398
00:39:49,828 --> 00:39:51,820
Here they are, 04.

399
00:39:52,831 --> 00:39:55,072
The ones in red,
are among the most dangerous.

400
00:39:55,958 --> 00:39:59,208
"Exhausted degreasing baths
with solvents, no liquid phase."

401
00:40:00,087 --> 00:40:01,367
No, no good.

402
00:40:03,382 --> 00:40:05,457
Then 4-11:

403
00:40:05,509 --> 00:40:08,509
"Waste containing halogenated
compounds from operations

404
00:40:08,595 --> 00:40:10,634
of manufacturing and finishing."

405
00:40:10,722 --> 00:40:12,714
These are good.

406
00:40:12,807 --> 00:40:16,756
It's stuff the earth absorbs,
we'll mix it with compost.

407
00:40:16,852 --> 00:40:17,967
Fertilizer!

408
00:40:20,981 --> 00:40:24,065
All that leaves is
Milan's sweeping refuse,

409
00:40:24,150 --> 00:40:26,143
that's 60 trucks.

410
00:40:27,278 --> 00:40:30,314
- The quarries at San Felice?.
- They're too small.

411
00:40:30,406 --> 00:40:32,445
I don't think so, look.

412
00:40:32,658 --> 00:40:34,615
Let me see.

413
00:40:40,874 --> 00:40:43,032
They're too small
and they're shallow,

414
00:40:44,127 --> 00:40:46,084
they're no good.

415
00:40:57,680 --> 00:41:01,630
Yes... I've got
ten contracts out of ten.

416
00:41:05,813 --> 00:41:06,975
Is he near you?.

417
00:41:09,941 --> 00:41:11,104
Put him on.

418
00:41:12,027 --> 00:41:13,225
I'll talk to him.

419
00:41:36,215 --> 00:41:39,169
I told him, everything's okay.

420
00:41:52,813 --> 00:41:55,849
- Do you like traveling?.
- Sure!

421
00:41:56,108 --> 00:41:58,100
We'll take more trips.

422
00:42:07,493 --> 00:42:09,569
Everyone here works in boats?.

423
00:42:10,454 --> 00:42:13,574
Everyone, firemen, ambulances...

424
00:42:14,750 --> 00:42:17,916
- Funerals.
- I've already seen two.

425
00:42:18,795 --> 00:42:20,871
Even the dead go by boat!

426
00:42:43,984 --> 00:42:46,060
Wow, they've got so many!

427
00:42:52,158 --> 00:42:53,237
Steady me.

428
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:47,448
There's nothing here.

429
00:44:02,221 --> 00:44:04,213
Nothing?.

430
00:44:04,306 --> 00:44:06,263
Are you sure?.

431
00:44:32,457 --> 00:44:34,366
Oh God!

432
00:44:34,417 --> 00:44:36,456
Look what's here!

433
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:45,923
See?. It's like you said!

434
00:44:49,055 --> 00:44:51,012
Look here!

435
00:44:51,140 --> 00:44:53,097
A Beretta 93!

436
00:44:53,184 --> 00:44:55,140
A Kalashnikov!

437
00:44:55,352 --> 00:44:57,428
See if they're loaded.

438
00:44:58,397 --> 00:45:00,555
- Check.
- It's unloaded.

439
00:45:16,121 --> 00:45:18,113
Look, an M12!

440
00:45:18,331 --> 00:45:20,370
This is the 921.

441
00:45:21,209 --> 00:45:22,371
That bearded bum!

442
00:45:22,460 --> 00:45:24,583
We'll see how
he blows my head off!

443
00:45:25,671 --> 00:45:28,755
Enough for Casale di Principe!
Everybody!

444
00:45:30,634 --> 00:45:32,757
Won't blow my head off now, eh?.

445
00:45:37,098 --> 00:45:39,137
Should I put two in?.

446
00:45:41,185 --> 00:45:43,177
And Nikita's?.

447
00:45:43,270 --> 00:45:45,263
And the 38?.

448
00:46:01,995 --> 00:46:05,198
- Want to see how I can shoot?.
- Show me!

449
00:46:06,249 --> 00:46:08,206
Show me!

450
00:46:09,294 --> 00:46:11,333
Aim there!

451
00:46:46,952 --> 00:46:48,861
I hit it!

452
00:47:05,552 --> 00:47:07,675
We'll blow
the Colombians' heads off!

453
00:47:16,103 --> 00:47:18,060
That's good.

454
00:47:22,401 --> 00:47:24,358
Everything okay?.

455
00:47:29,574 --> 00:47:31,613
With love and feeling.

456
00:47:45,130 --> 00:47:47,371
- What is it?.
- Your wife's on the phone.

457
00:47:48,257 --> 00:47:49,502
Tell her not to wait up.

458
00:47:50,343 --> 00:47:52,584
Don't get tired out, need anything?.

459
00:47:53,470 --> 00:47:54,633
No, thanks.

460
00:47:54,721 --> 00:47:56,797
- You'll lock up?.
- Yes.

461
00:47:57,724 --> 00:47:58,803
Goodnight.

462
00:48:22,872 --> 00:48:24,781
Xian?.

463
00:49:00,239 --> 00:49:01,401
I have been waiting for you.

464
00:49:03,533 --> 00:49:06,653
- I got lost.
- I am happy you came.

465
00:49:21,049 --> 00:49:22,164
Please sit down.

466
00:49:25,303 --> 00:49:27,426
We are cooking fish.

467
00:49:37,772 --> 00:49:39,812
I've already eaten.

468
00:49:40,900 --> 00:49:43,023
Try a typical Chinese dish.

469
00:49:43,986 --> 00:49:45,149
Okay?.

470
00:49:51,451 --> 00:49:54,452
Just cooked, it is good.

471
00:49:54,496 --> 00:49:56,488
Meat with bell peppers.

472
00:49:56,581 --> 00:49:58,620
I've already eaten.

473
00:50:01,794 --> 00:50:02,908
Taste.

474
00:50:03,796 --> 00:50:05,835
We use chopsticks.

475
00:50:05,923 --> 00:50:08,045
- I don't know how to use them.
- Try!

476
00:50:11,177 --> 00:50:13,217
I am pleased,

477
00:50:13,263 --> 00:50:15,385
we have a little toast.

478
00:50:16,515 --> 00:50:19,386
We go to the factory.

479
00:50:26,941 --> 00:50:28,898
Why not?.

480
00:50:33,072 --> 00:50:35,111
I put a pillow in here.

481
00:50:35,241 --> 00:50:37,198
It's dangerous.

482
00:50:38,368 --> 00:50:42,366
I already told you,
no one can know, just us.

483
00:50:42,539 --> 00:50:44,615
It's better for both of us.

484
00:50:45,500 --> 00:50:49,711
- Won't I need air?.
- No, there's an opening.

485
00:50:50,796 --> 00:50:53,880
I'll open the front window,
so air will come in.

486
00:50:56,009 --> 00:50:57,966
Forgive me.

487
00:51:00,096 --> 00:51:01,341
Are we sure?.

488
00:51:03,391 --> 00:51:06,557
It is best for both of us,
because it is dangerous.

489
00:51:09,647 --> 00:51:12,600
- Does air come through here?.
- Yes.

490
00:51:12,816 --> 00:51:14,892
And I'll open the window too.

491
00:52:20,377 --> 00:52:22,452
Please come in, Mr. Pasquale.

492
00:52:23,713 --> 00:52:25,752
All are waiting for you.

493
00:52:28,843 --> 00:52:30,882
All are very happy.

494
00:52:46,442 --> 00:52:48,683
I told them who you are
and all are happy.

495
00:52:51,696 --> 00:52:53,689
What a nice factory!

496
00:52:53,865 --> 00:52:55,988
More than 80 people.

497
00:53:39,740 --> 00:53:41,779
I'm moved.

498
00:53:45,954 --> 00:53:47,993
What can I say?.

499
00:53:49,165 --> 00:53:51,241
To do this work

500
00:53:52,334 --> 00:53:55,205
you need lots of patience...

501
00:54:00,675 --> 00:54:02,667
...and lots of love.

502
00:54:08,974 --> 00:54:11,014
For the first lesson...

503
00:54:14,062 --> 00:54:16,185
...I'll cut out a bodice.

504
00:54:24,530 --> 00:54:25,644
Let's begin.

505
00:54:37,041 --> 00:54:40,077
You must place patterns carefully.

506
00:54:46,508 --> 00:54:48,584
Spread the cloth well...

507
00:55:12,490 --> 00:55:14,529
Maria, are you asleep?.

508
00:55:19,746 --> 00:55:21,904
Where have I been, in China?.

509
00:55:25,001 --> 00:55:27,077
They were all bowing to me.

510
00:55:29,255 --> 00:55:31,164
Master!

511
00:55:31,298 --> 00:55:34,299
They called me "master"!

512
00:55:39,514 --> 00:55:42,633
- Did you know the Chinese can cook?.
- The Chinese?.

513
00:55:42,767 --> 00:55:44,806
Darn right!

514
00:55:44,935 --> 00:55:47,853
They cooked a delicious bass!

515
00:55:52,025 --> 00:55:53,270
There were boxes everywhere

516
00:55:54,110 --> 00:55:56,186
and they put me in the trunk!

517
00:55:57,363 --> 00:55:59,439
Both coming and going.

518
00:56:03,494 --> 00:56:04,739
I need some sleep.

519
00:56:08,707 --> 00:56:09,821
Here.

520
00:56:10,792 --> 00:56:12,915
I have to sleep a few hours.

521
00:56:17,089 --> 00:56:19,212
What's this money?.

522
00:56:30,685 --> 00:56:32,724
Where did you get it?.

523
00:56:32,853 --> 00:56:34,893
I have to sleep.

524
00:56:37,983 --> 00:56:39,975
Help me understand.

525
00:56:40,068 --> 00:56:42,191
I talked to my son this morning,

526
00:56:42,278 --> 00:56:45,196
he said: "Mom I'm leaving,

527
00:56:45,406 --> 00:56:47,446
I'm going to be a secessionist."

528
00:56:48,534 --> 00:56:50,443
Really?.

529
00:56:54,623 --> 00:56:56,662
What did you say?.

530
00:56:56,833 --> 00:56:58,826
He's convinced,

531
00:56:59,836 --> 00:57:01,959
he said: "We're great,

532
00:57:02,046 --> 00:57:06,126
we'll win the war,
the others are nobodies".

533
00:57:06,175 --> 00:57:09,341
War?. A bunch of morons
warring against us?.

534
00:57:10,304 --> 00:57:12,343
You have to stop him.

535
00:57:13,515 --> 00:57:15,554
This side is the right side.

536
00:57:17,518 --> 00:57:19,677
Have you seen what's happening?.

537
00:57:19,812 --> 00:57:21,852
There are killings every day.

538
00:57:23,816 --> 00:57:26,900
Don't say anything to anybody,
not even your husband.

539
00:57:28,111 --> 00:57:30,151
Who'd ever tell him!

540
00:57:32,282 --> 00:57:35,401
When he gets out, what'll he do?.
Father and son will kill each other?.

541
00:57:36,285 --> 00:57:38,408
No, because your son
will stay right here.

