I've warned them more than once.

807
01:27:55,828 --> 01:27:57,904
I can't consider them kids anymore.

808
01:27:58,914 --> 01:28:00,990
They have to die, that's final!

809
01:28:01,083 --> 01:28:05,127
You're right,
but first let's tell the families.

810
01:28:05,212 --> 01:28:07,251
I don't know who they are.

811
01:28:09,340 --> 01:28:12,424
Will you take care of it?.

812
01:28:12,552 --> 01:28:14,674
I'll handle it!

813
01:28:43,621 --> 01:28:44,866
Toto, is that you?.

814
01:28:51,170 --> 01:28:54,254
- What happened to Silvana?.
- In the storeroom.

815
01:29:10,979 --> 01:29:13,896
How come it's so dark?.

816
01:29:13,982 --> 01:29:16,021
Why are you in the dark?.

817
01:29:16,067 --> 01:29:18,024
It's okay like this.

818
01:29:18,277 --> 01:29:20,186
Your change.

819
01:29:22,406 --> 01:29:25,442
- The bread?.
- There wasn't any.

820
01:29:25,534 --> 01:29:28,570
- What'll we eat?.
- There's pasta.

821
01:29:31,706 --> 01:29:34,707
- Take your change.
- It's for you.

822
01:29:45,260 --> 01:29:47,466
Why did you put her
in the storeroom?.

823
01:29:48,346 --> 01:29:50,385
She's fine where she is.

824
01:29:50,598 --> 01:29:53,552
She's just an animal!

825
01:31:07,625 --> 01:31:09,748
Come here a minute,
I have to talk to you.

826
01:31:11,754 --> 01:31:13,794
Don't come out, it's dangerous.

827
01:31:13,923 --> 01:31:16,046
Come on, no one can see you.

828
01:31:20,137 --> 01:31:22,176
What are you doing, you're going?.

829
01:31:25,433 --> 01:31:27,307
Listen to me!

830
01:31:27,560 --> 01:31:30,477
They said I have to leave.

831
01:31:30,646 --> 01:31:32,722
I have to leave my house.

832
01:31:33,691 --> 01:31:35,730
I can't do anything.

833
01:31:35,817 --> 01:31:37,857
I'm not leaving!

834
01:31:38,904 --> 01:31:40,943
Come here a minute!

835
01:31:47,244 --> 01:31:50,447
Tell those friends of yours,
I'm not leaving!

836
01:31:52,374 --> 01:31:54,532
Tell those nice people!

837
01:31:54,626 --> 01:31:58,623
I won't betray my son
and I'm not moving from here!

838
01:32:00,757 --> 01:32:02,832
Not coming in for coffee?.

839
01:32:02,883 --> 01:32:04,840
Run off, run away!

840
01:32:45,547 --> 01:32:46,745
Hello, accountant.

841
01:32:47,674 --> 01:32:48,753
Please come in.

842
01:32:49,926 --> 01:32:53,010
Why this sudden call?.

843
01:32:53,846 --> 01:32:55,044
You're worrying me.

844
01:32:55,931 --> 01:32:58,054
The designers pay me after 60 days,

845
01:32:58,141 --> 01:33:00,264
I have a little money,

846
01:33:00,352 --> 01:33:03,222
but this wasn't the agreement.

847
01:33:03,313 --> 01:33:05,435
Money isn't the problem.

848
01:33:06,566 --> 01:33:08,523
What is it then?.

849
01:33:08,609 --> 01:33:10,602
It seems

850
01:33:11,695 --> 01:33:13,818
the problem is in your own house.

851
01:33:14,906 --> 01:33:16,899
In my house?.

852
01:33:16,992 --> 01:33:19,031
What problem is it?.

853
01:33:20,161 --> 01:33:22,154
One of your associates,

854
01:33:24,081 --> 01:33:25,196
Pasquale Del Prete,

855
01:33:25,332 --> 01:33:27,241
has sold out to the Chinese.

856
01:33:37,802 --> 01:33:39,759
We're done.

857
01:33:43,891 --> 01:33:45,089
The finishing touches...

858
01:33:54,400 --> 01:33:56,440
I never doubted.

859
01:34:16,378 --> 01:34:18,335
Everything okay?.

860
01:34:21,550 --> 01:34:24,716
Remember the first time
I put you to work in the factory?.

861
01:34:24,803 --> 01:34:26,795
You were just a kid.

862
01:34:28,931 --> 01:34:30,010
Right.

863
01:34:40,316 --> 01:34:42,475
- Everything alright?.
- Yes.

864
01:35:07,341 --> 01:35:10,544
Tell him to go slower, not too fast.

865
01:35:25,107 --> 01:35:26,269
Well done, Giulia.

866
01:35:27,192 --> 01:35:28,306
She's good.

867
01:36:00,555 --> 01:36:02,631
In the morning I do Tai Chi.

868
01:36:02,724 --> 01:36:03,755
Really?.

869
01:36:04,642 --> 01:36:06,967
- It's nice.
- It is good for your health.

870
01:36:07,853 --> 01:36:09,976
It is like in China.

871
01:36:11,023 --> 01:36:15,103
When you go to the park
in the morning, it is full of people

872
01:36:16,278 --> 01:36:18,270
old people too.

873
01:36:19,280 --> 01:36:21,356
All doing Tai Chi.

874
01:36:21,449 --> 01:36:22,611
Everyone

875
01:36:23,659 --> 01:36:26,576
Iikes the culture of Tai Chi.

876
01:36:28,664 --> 01:36:30,905
It's a tradition of Chinese culture.

877
01:36:31,792 --> 01:36:33,950
When will you do egg rolls for me?.

878
01:37:30,344 --> 01:37:32,253
Wait up.

879
01:37:34,348 --> 01:37:37,597
I spoke to the doctors,
you'll soon be released.

880
01:37:44,857 --> 01:37:46,896
Damn you,

881
01:37:47,026 --> 01:37:49,018
you really goofed up.

882
01:37:51,154 --> 01:37:55,199
They loved the models,
they've asked for more...

883
01:37:55,283 --> 01:37:57,276
You knew everything.

884
01:37:57,368 --> 01:37:59,527
That's how I saved your life.

885
01:38:00,538 --> 01:38:03,538
Those people don't kid around.

886
01:38:03,666 --> 01:38:05,623
Leave me alone.

887
01:38:05,709 --> 01:38:09,789
You should thank me,
those guys will kill you.

888
01:38:09,838 --> 01:38:11,961
You and I pulled through.

889
01:38:12,048 --> 01:38:15,168
- Find another tailor.
- Why do you say that?.

890
01:38:16,052 --> 01:38:19,218
- I want to be alone.
- How can I do this without you?.

891
01:38:19,305 --> 01:38:21,297
I really don't care.

892
01:38:21,390 --> 01:38:25,434
- After all I've done for you.
- What have you done for me?.

893
01:38:25,519 --> 01:38:28,722
I took you off the streets,
I fed you for years.

894
01:38:29,564 --> 01:38:32,683
-You've used me since I was a kid.
- Don't say that!

895
01:38:33,859 --> 01:38:37,109
When you're better,
come see me, I'll give you a raise.

896
01:38:39,198 --> 01:38:43,195
Rosa, give me that bike,
I have to go.

897
01:40:11,989 --> 01:40:14,065
No admittance here,

898
01:40:14,909 --> 01:40:16,106
that's it.

899
01:40:30,756 --> 01:40:32,795
Want to give up?.

900
01:40:33,675 --> 01:40:35,882
Are we meat for the slaughter house?.

901
01:40:45,102 --> 01:40:47,178
Let's shoot,
we'll rack up corpses too.

902
01:40:47,313 --> 01:40:48,427
Corpses?.

903
01:40:49,481 --> 01:40:53,431
- I'm not moving without orders.
- What orders?.

904
01:40:53,568 --> 01:40:55,691
We don't know how to move.

905
01:40:57,780 --> 01:40:59,820
We don't know anything.

906
01:41:03,035 --> 01:41:05,952
Do we have to keep taking it?.

907
01:41:06,079 --> 01:41:08,238
Do we have to wait for orders?.

908
01:41:11,376 --> 01:41:13,415
Let's rack up corpses.

909
01:41:13,503 --> 01:41:17,500
What are we waiting for,
to be put down one by one?.

910
01:41:21,635 --> 01:41:23,841
If we don't move, nothing will change

911
01:41:23,929 --> 01:41:26,005
No use feeling depressed.

912
01:41:27,974 --> 01:41:30,097
We all have to be convinced.

913
01:41:30,184 --> 01:41:33,138
But without orders, I'm not moving.

914
01:41:35,397 --> 01:41:37,437
This is open war,

915
01:41:38,275 --> 01:41:40,351
you mustn't think about anyone.

916
01:41:40,485 --> 01:41:43,652
- Who do we kill?.
- Let's begin in our area.

917
01:41:44,739 --> 01:41:46,815
From our own stronghold.

918
01:41:47,700 --> 01:41:49,906
We don't know who's with us
and who's against us,

919
01:41:49,994 --> 01:41:52,070
who do we make pay?.

920
01:41:52,913 --> 01:41:56,080
Where do you think
the order to kill came from?.

921
01:41:56,166 --> 01:41:57,281
Think!

922
01:41:59,169 --> 01:42:01,208
Where did it come from?.

923
01:42:01,421 --> 01:42:04,375
- From there of course.
- From our own area.

924
01:42:04,465 --> 01:42:06,505
She betrayed us.

925
01:42:06,592 --> 01:42:08,715
We don't touch women.

926
01:42:09,553 --> 01:42:10,716
Don't yell!

927
01:42:11,763 --> 01:42:13,839
What are you saying?.

928
01:42:17,060 --> 01:42:21,140
Don't take it out on someone
no part of this, but the son.

929
01:42:21,272 --> 01:42:25,221
- How do we find him?.
- His mother's in our district.

930
01:42:25,276 --> 01:42:27,315
It was her son who killed Gaetano.

931
01:42:27,444 --> 01:42:29,484
Let's think what we'll do.

932
01:42:30,530 --> 01:42:32,653
We could use the kid.

933
01:42:33,575 --> 01:42:35,697
He's the only one who can get to her.

934
01:42:36,869 --> 01:42:38,862
He brings her shopping,

935
01:42:38,955 --> 01:42:41,077
he's in good with the woman...

936
01:42:42,041 --> 01:42:44,116
So, if we have to do it

937
01:42:44,209 --> 01:42:46,249
we'll need his help.

938
01:42:49,214 --> 01:42:51,290
Toto, what do you think you'll do?.

939
01:42:52,467 --> 01:42:54,589
Are you with us or against us?.

940
01:43:01,725 --> 01:43:03,764
What do you say?.

941
01:43:04,978 --> 01:43:07,054
Are you with us or not?.

942
01:43:09,023 --> 01:43:12,107
- We'll see what we can do.
- No, "we'll see".

943
01:43:12,193 --> 01:43:14,315
Either you're with us
or you're against us,

944
01:43:15,320 --> 01:43:17,360
one or the other.

945
01:43:17,406 --> 01:43:21,533
If you're against us you can't leave,
we can't trust you.

946
01:43:21,618 --> 01:43:23,776
It can't have been her.

947
01:43:24,746 --> 01:43:26,785
This is our decision,

948
01:43:26,873 --> 01:43:28,912
you have to be with us.

949
01:43:28,999 --> 01:43:32,119
That's what we say,
you don't need to think.

950
01:43:37,257 --> 01:43:39,296
What are you going to do?.

951
01:43:40,385 --> 01:43:43,551
- We'll see.
- I said no "we'll see".

952
01:44:00,111 --> 01:44:01,225
Come on down.

953
01:44:01,320 --> 01:44:03,359
I have to tell you something!

954
01:44:05,407 --> 01:44:07,364
No, come down!

955
01:44:08,535 --> 01:44:10,658
Hurry, I have to leave!

956
01:45:51,753 --> 01:45:52,867
Sit down!

957
01:46:31,372 --> 01:46:33,411
You've known me for years,

958
01:46:33,498 --> 01:46:35,621
you know what I've always done.

959
01:46:37,627 --> 01:46:39,584
I brought the money.

960
01:46:39,671 --> 01:46:41,793
I brought it to your family too.

961
01:46:43,841 --> 01:46:45,964
I did it because I was ordered to.

962
01:46:51,139 --> 01:46:53,215
War isn't for me.

963
01:46:53,391 --> 01:46:56,345
But you're in it, know that?.

964
01:46:58,479 --> 01:46:59,558
Yes.

965
01:46:59,647 --> 01:47:01,520
So?.

966
01:47:01,690 --> 01:47:03,599
You tell me.

967
01:47:03,650 --> 01:47:05,643
What can I tell you?.

968
01:47:09,030 --> 01:47:11,948
What did you come here for?.

969
01:47:14,035 --> 01:47:15,233
To talk to you.

970
01:47:16,162 --> 01:47:17,324
About what?.

971
01:47:21,375 --> 01:47:23,414
I want to save myself.

972
01:47:23,502 --> 01:47:25,660
You'll have to buy your life,

973
01:47:26,546 --> 01:47:28,585
I won't give it to you.

974
01:47:32,968 --> 01:47:35,008
What I did there,

975
01:47:36,055 --> 01:47:38,130
I can do for you here.

976
01:47:39,057 --> 01:47:41,180
We don't need money-carriers,

977
01:47:41,226 --> 01:47:44,429
we have to score,
kill people, and we need money.

978
01:47:45,480 --> 01:47:47,472
You're wasting your time.

979
01:47:50,693 --> 01:47:52,685
You're more dead than alive.

980
01:47:52,778 --> 01:47:55,779
But we were brothers before.

981
01:47:55,864 --> 01:47:56,895
Before!

982
01:47:56,990 --> 01:48:00,026
Then they started
messing around with shit.

983
01:48:05,164 --> 01:48:07,287
Our relatives were good people...

984
01:48:08,292 --> 01:48:10,415
so they killed them!

985
01:48:12,462 --> 01:48:13,625
So, don't come asking

986
01:48:14,506 --> 01:48:15,704
to pass to the other side.

987
01:48:16,591 --> 01:48:18,714
We have to score, kill,

988
01:48:18,801 --> 01:48:20,841
and we need money.

989
01:48:21,804 --> 01:48:23,002
If not, you die,

990
01:48:23,889 --> 01:48:25,965
because you're part of the war.

991
01:48:26,016 --> 01:48:28,092
You bring money and I kill people,

992
01:48:28,226 --> 01:48:31,180
we're the same, you and me,
in this war.

993
01:48:32,355 --> 01:48:34,431
- I understand.
- You understand.

994
01:48:45,784 --> 01:48:46,982
Wait a moment.

995
01:49:18,313 --> 01:49:20,305
Everything okay?.

996
01:49:22,483 --> 01:49:24,440
And you?.

997
01:49:31,783 --> 01:49:33,740
That's four.

998
01:49:44,336 --> 01:49:46,376
Face on the table!

999
01:49:47,256 --> 01:49:48,501
Done?.

1000
01:49:49,508 --> 01:49:50,587
Let's go!

1001
01:49:58,891 --> 01:50:00,800
Come on out!

1002
01:50:01,018 --> 01:50:03,057
Lucky, eh?.

1003
01:51:29,556 --> 01:51:31,595
That's poison.

1004
01:51:32,809 --> 01:51:34,885
What'd he say?.

1005
01:51:35,728 --> 01:51:38,978
My father wants to say the dumping
you're doing on our land

1006
01:51:39,857 --> 01:51:41,055
isn't garbage.

1007
01:51:41,942 --> 01:51:43,140
It's poison.

1008
01:51:43,235 --> 01:51:45,274
It's not garbage?.

1009
01:51:47,197 --> 01:51:48,442
You heard right.

1010
01:51:49,282 --> 01:51:50,480
Don't worry.

1011
01:51:51,367 --> 01:51:54,534
A year's gone by with this dumping?.

1012
01:51:55,704 --> 01:51:58,740
So far,
all we've done is pay our debts.

1013
01:51:59,875 --> 01:52:00,954
Just barely.

1014
01:52:01,793 --> 01:52:05,078
- Euro.
- I understand, Don Raffaele.

1015
01:52:08,090 --> 01:52:10,297
Everything costs double in euro.

1016
01:52:11,260 --> 01:52:12,375
And so?.

1017
01:52:14,263 --> 01:52:15,543
We need something more.

1018
01:52:17,516 --> 01:52:20,552
These are the prices,
explain it to your kids,

1019
01:52:20,643 --> 01:52:23,727
if I do it for you,
I have to do it for everyone.

1020
01:52:23,813 --> 01:52:25,852
Don't put me
in a difficult situation.

1021
01:52:25,940 --> 01:52:29,984
Okay, if you give us more,
everyone has to get more.

1022
01:52:30,027 --> 01:52:32,066
So, little can be done.

1023
01:52:32,154 --> 01:52:34,312
But, we barely make ends meet,

1024
01:52:35,156 --> 01:52:37,279
we can't go on like this.

1025
01:52:37,367 --> 01:52:39,406
We were thinking,

1026
01:52:40,536 --> 01:52:43,620
is it possible to do more dumping?.

1027
01:52:45,749 --> 01:52:47,658
Euro...

1028
01:52:47,835 --> 01:52:49,910
More dumping?.

1029
01:52:50,795 --> 01:52:53,880
We have another piece of land
for other dumping sites.

1030
01:52:53,965 --> 01:52:55,163
Near here?.

1031
01:52:56,134 --> 01:52:58,091
Around here.

1032
01:52:58,135 --> 01:53:00,175
More dumping we do,

1033
01:53:00,304 --> 01:53:02,380
faster the ground gets filled.

1034
01:53:02,473 --> 01:53:05,390
You have another piece of land?.

1035
01:53:06,435 --> 01:53:08,676
- Near here?.
- Further on.

1036
01:53:09,562 --> 01:53:12,682
This other land
would be more convenient,

1037
01:53:12,732 --> 01:53:15,851
it's bigger and trucks
can get in easier.

1038
01:53:17,027 --> 01:53:18,901
But...

1039
01:53:20,989 --> 01:53:23,065
Still 100 euros per dumping.

1040
01:53:23,158 --> 01:53:25,197
What do you mean 100 euros!

1041
01:53:25,326 --> 01:53:27,366
Don't speak out of turn.

1042
01:53:27,412 --> 01:53:29,488
- He can't increase!
- Who said so?.

1043
01:53:30,414 --> 01:53:32,490
We'll increase the trucks.

1044
01:53:33,626 --> 01:53:36,792
You have to increase
the price of each dumping.

1045
01:53:37,879 --> 01:53:39,836
Want to lose everything?.

1046
01:53:39,923 --> 01:53:42,046
They have nowhere else to turn.

1047
01:53:42,884 --> 01:53:43,963
Excuse me.

1048
01:53:44,052 --> 01:53:46,009
Don't worry.

1049
01:53:47,305 --> 01:53:49,344
Alright, now we'll reach...

1050
01:53:54,478 --> 01:53:56,470
an agreement.

1051
01:53:56,563 --> 01:53:58,686
Give him a glass of water.

1052
01:53:58,773 --> 01:54:00,849
I'll do it, don't worry.

1053
01:54:11,076 --> 01:54:12,155
Luca!

1054
01:54:19,542 --> 01:54:21,665
You have to clean up this field!

1055
01:54:22,670 --> 01:54:24,579
I'm not Luca.

1056
01:54:24,713 --> 01:54:26,752
Do a little work.

1057
01:54:26,840 --> 01:54:28,832
My name's Roberto.

1058
01:54:31,010 --> 01:54:33,133
This field is such a mess.

1059
01:54:34,138 --> 01:54:36,095
All such a mess.

1060
01:54:37,183 --> 01:54:38,381
Ma'am, it's raining.

1061
01:54:40,227 --> 01:54:41,390
Should I stop?.

1062
01:54:41,520 --> 01:54:43,512
Come out of there.

1063
01:54:46,524 --> 01:54:48,564
I'll take you inside.

1064
01:54:48,818 --> 01:54:50,775
I'll be right along.

1065
01:54:50,903 --> 01:54:52,943
They've made ditches here,

1066
01:54:53,823 --> 01:54:55,898
someone should come

1067
01:54:55,991 --> 01:54:58,031
to fill them.

1068
01:55:11,589 --> 01:55:12,668
Let's go!

1069
01:55:25,226 --> 01:55:27,218
What beautiful peaches, thank you!

1070
01:55:27,311 --> 01:55:29,350
I'll take them to the kids.

1071
01:55:29,480 --> 01:55:31,519
See how beautiful they are!

1072
01:55:32,607 --> 01:55:34,516
Let's go.

1073
01:55:34,693 --> 01:55:36,732
Put them in the car.

1074
01:55:36,778 --> 01:55:38,651
Come on!

1075
01:55:52,250 --> 01:55:54,289
